Object Relationship Mapping (ORM) 
•
Our design is a simplify version of  Object Relationship Mapping 
(ORM) 
•
Translate and map objects between relational table.
•
Translate the logical representation of the objects into an atomized form 
that is capable of being stored in the database.
•
Hide the SQL statement
•
Exposes API for other component

[Full Page OCR]:
Object Relationship Mapping (ORM) Our design is a simplify version of Object Relationship Mapping (ORM) Translate and map objects between relational table. Translate the logical representation of the objects into an atomized form that is capable of being stored in the database. Hide the SQL statement Exposes API for other component

Object-relational Mapping
ORM
•
Consider an address book entry that represents a single person 
along with zero or more phone numbers and zero or more 
addresses. 
•
This could be modeled in an object-oriented implementation by a 
"Person object" with attributes/fields to hold each data item that 
the entry comprises:  the person''s name, a list of phone numbers, 
and a list of addresses. The list of phone numbers would itself 
contain "PhoneNumber objects" and so on. 
•
The address-book entry is treated as a single object by the 
programming language (it can be referenced by a single variable 
containing a pointer to the object, for instance). Various methods 
can be associated with the object, such as a method to return the 
preferred phone number, the home address, and so on.
•
https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Object-relational_mapping

