How to handle result set
•
Access the data in a ResultSet object through a cursor
•
cursor is a pointer that points to one row of data in the ResultSet.
•
Initially, the cursor is positioned before the first row. 
•
The method ResultSet.next moves the cursor to the next row. 
•
This method returns false if the cursor is positioned after the last 
row. 
•
This method repeatedly calls the ResultSet.next method with a 
while loop to iterate through all the data in the ResultSet.

