Client-Known URL name - The client sees a URL for the servlet but does not know how that servlet name maps to a real directory and file back on the server, the URL is a fake name made up for the clients
Deployer-Known Secret Internal name - The deployer can create a name that''s known only to the deployer and others in the real operational environment, this name again is a fake name made up just for the deployment of the servlet
Actual filename - The developers servlet class has a fully-qualified name that includes both the class name and package name. The class file has a real path and file name, depending on where the package directory structure lives on the server.
