ABAP is an event-driven language
This means that the general flow of an ABAP program is controlled by external event
The system always starts a processing block when the corresponding event occurs
What is a processing block?
You can define processing block in your ABAP program by using event keyword 
All statements between two event keywords or between an event keyword and a FORM statement form a processing block
When an event occurs, the system processes the processing block after the corresponding event keyword
Each statement in an ABAP program is part of a processing block or a subroutine
3

