Each ABAP program has a modular structure
ABAP programs are divided into:
Processing blocks that are controlled by events when the program is a report program (Program of type 1)
Modules that are controlled by the screen flow logic when the program is an dialog program (Module pool of type M)
You can modularize either your source code or tasks which are to be performed repeatedly
14

[Full Slide OCR]:
O Each ABAP program has a modular structure a0 yan O ABAP programs are divided into: © Processing blocks that are controlled by events when the program is a report program (Program of type 1) © Modules that are controlled by the screen flow logic when the program is an dialog program (Module pool of type M) O You can modularize either your source code or tasks which are to be performed repeatedly 14

To modularize source codes the following two methods apply:
Include program
Macro
To modularize tasks the following two methods apply:
Subroutine
Functional module
