You can create callable modules of program code within your ABAP program by defining macro
To define a macro which contains part of the source code, you use the DEFINE statement as follows:
Syntax:
DEFINE <macro>.
	<statements>
END-OF-DEFINITION.
You must specify complete statements between DEFINE and END-OF-DEFINITION
Notice: The coding within macro cannot be debugged
