Subroutine is program module which can be called from ABAP program
Internal subroutine
The source code of internal subroutine is in the same ABAP program as the calling procedure (internal call)
External subroutine
The source code of external subroutine is in an ABAP program other than the calling procedure (external call)
19

[Full Slide OCR]:
O Subroutine is program module which can be called from ABAP program O Internal subroutine © The source code of internal subroutine is in the same ABAP program as the calling procedure (internal call) O External subroutine O The source code of external subroutine is in an ABAP program other than the calling procedure (external call) 19

A subroutine is a block of code introduced by FORM and concluded by ENDFORM
To define a subroutine, use the following syntax:
Syntax:
FORM <subr> [<pass>].
	<statement block>
ENDFORM.
<subr> - The name of the subroutine
<pass> - You specify how to pass data to and from the subroutine {mainly for external call}.
20

[Full Slide OCR]:
O Asubroutine is a block of code introduced by FORM and concluded by ENDFORM © To define a subroutine, use the following syntax: © Syntax: © FORM <subr> [<pass>]. O  <statement block> O ENDFORM. O <subr> - The name of the subroutine O <pass> - You specify how to pass data to and from the subroutine {mainly for external call}. 20

Calling Internal Subroutine
To call an internal subroutine, use the PERFORM statement as follows:
Syntax:
PERFORM <subr> [<pass>].
Calling External Subroutine
To call an external subroutine, use the PERFORM statement as follows:
Syntax:
PERFORM <subr> (IN PROGRAM <prog>) [<pass>] [IF FOUND].
21

[Full Slide OCR]:
