Storing Data Objects as Clusters You can group any complex internal data objects of an ABAP/4 program together in data clusters and store them temporarily in ABAP/4 memory or for longer periods in databases. data cluster = set of data objects fleld stings data hase 3 8

You can store data cluster in ABAP memory
ABAP memory is not dependent on the ABAP program or program module which generates it during a transaction
This means that an object stored in ABAP memory can be read again by any ABAP program during the same transaction
For example, you can pass data between:
Report and other Report called with SUBMIT
Transaction and Report
Program and Function Module
Note : The memory is released again when you leave the transaction
