Some Comments on JSP

[Full Page OCR]:
Some Comments on JSP

•
Good points
–
2-tier is easier to setup than 3-tier
•
2-tier – presentation logic and business logic mix up in the same 
layer
•
3-tier – presentation logic and business logic separated
–
Many web sites do not need 3-tier architecture
•
Bank application needs 3-tier, of course
•
Bad points
–
JSP is too easy to mix up presentation logic with business logic, 
since it uses Java as the scripting language
–
As a presentation layer only, JSP is too easy to mix up 
presentation template and presentation logic
66
JSP as a 2-tier Architecture

[Full Page OCR]:
JSP as a 2-tier Architecture ° Good points -—  2-tier is easier to setup than 3-tier e 2-tier— presentation logic and business logic mix up in the same layer e  3-tier— presentation logic and business logic separated — Many web sites do not need 3-tier architecture ¢ Bank application needs 3-tier, of course ° Bad points — JSP is too easy to mix up presentation logic with business logic, since it uses Java as the scripting language — layer only, JSP is too easy to mix up presentation template and presentation logic

•
If vigorous business logic exists, confine the use of 
