All of the commercial and industrial activities that seek profits by providing goods and services for sale.
Earnings that remain in a firm after the costs of operations and taxes  Profits = Revenues – Costs
Purpose of a Business
The purpose of a business is to earn a profit or make money for its owners.
It rewards a business for providing the desired goods and services to consumers in an economical and efficient manner.
In non-profit or not-for-profit organizations, any revenue earned above expenses is used to improve the organization – Red Cross
