INSERT INTO parsed_documents (document_name, document_hash, parsed_json, summary, chunks, concepts, relationships, created_at, updated_at, deleted_at, modules, source_id, raw_text) VALUES ( '1718_ITP4511_Test.pdf', '5ba912836d9a68b5cb405a383708f42b31e55d22f7fbf8d33dc2671e81e2d9df', '{"chunks": [{"id": "CHUNK_001", "text": "A simple web application is developed with Java Server Page. It shows an image of a medal based on the value of an input mark. The application is composed of medalDB.jsp, q1.jsp and q1Handler.jsp. The medalDB.jsp defines a String[] getAllMedals method in JSP declaration. The method returns all image locations in String array. The q1.jsp shows images of medals in table format and an input form for user submission. The locations of medal images are specified in the getAllMedals method. The q1Handler.jsp obtains input parameter, mark, validates input parameter and displays the corresponding value of the mark. It also displays a corresponding medal image if the mark is within a specific range. The mark range is between 50 to 100 inclusively. If user does not submit a parameter, mark, then an error message will be displayed.", "pages": [2], "end_pos": 732, "summary": "Overview of a JSP-based web app with three components handling medal display based on user input mark.", "start_pos": 0, "chunk_type": "overview", "has_examples": true, "main_concepts": ["CONC_001", "CONC_008", "CONC_009", "CONC_010"], "has_definitions": true, "secondary_concepts": ["CONC_002", "CONC_014", "CONC_015"]}, {"id": "CHUNK_002", "text": "The code fragment of q1.jsp is shown below: <!DOCTYPE html> <html><head><title>q1</title> </head> <body>  <h1>Medals </h1>  <table border=\"1\"> <tr> <td> Gold </td> <td> Silver </td> <td> Bronze </td> </tr>  </table>  <hr/>   </body></html> (b) With reference to the sample output of the q1.jsp, write code to complete the following tasks. (i) Write a JSP Directive to include the medalDB.jsp. [2%] (ii) Write JSP Scriptlet to output the table as per the Figure Q1a. You are MUST use the getAllMedals () method. [5%] (iii) Write HTML code to show an input form.", "pages": [3], "end_pos": 1368, "summary": "Code fragment and tasks for q1.jsp involving inclusion, scriptlet usage, and form creation.", "start_pos": 733, "chunk_type": "code_context", "has_examples": true, "main_concepts": ["CONC_009", "CONC_005", "CONC_003"], "has_definitions": true, "secondary_concepts": ["CONC_001", "CONC_008"]}, {"id": "CHUNK_003", "text": "The code fragment of q1Handler.jsp is shown below: <!DOCTYPE html> <html><head><title>q1Handler</title> </head> <body>   <%   String input = \"\"; int mark = 0;      %>      <h2> Your input mark is  </h2>        </body> </html> (c) With reference to the q1Handler.jsp and the figure Q1b, complete the following task: (i) Obtain the parameter, mark, and assign it to input. [1%] (ii) If the parameter, input, is not submitted, output the following message “You did not submit any value!!” [2%] (iii) If the parameter, input is submitted, parse input to an integer and assign it to the variable mark. Use the getAllMedals() method and output corresponding image. [5%] (iv) Use JSP Expression to display the value of the mark. [1%] (v) Write HTML to display a hyperlink linked to q1.jsp for trying again. [1%] (vi) Write JSP Directive in q1Handler.jsp to pass the exception to handleError.jsp.", "pages": [3], "end_pos": 2218, "summary": "Tasks for implementing q1Handler.jsp including parameter handling, validation, output, and error forwarding.", "start_pos": 1369, "chunk_type": "code_context", "has_examples": true, "main_concepts": ["CONC_010", "CONC_004", "CONC_005", "CONC_015"], "has_definitions": true, "secondary_concepts": ["CONC_001", "CONC_008"]}, {"id": "CHUNK_004", "text": "A web application built with the technologies, JSP, JavaBeans and Servlet for displaying product information. The JSP page, enquiry.jsp, is an input form. It allows multiple selection for product codes. The Java servlet class, ict.servlet.ProductController, handles inputted parameter, obtains the corresponding product information from database and displays it accordingly. The class, ict.db.ProductDB, provides methods to handle the database operations. A JavaBean class, ict.bean.Product, is used to support the form operations. (a) Write down the well-formed HTML in the enquiry.jsp... (b) Write code for completing the implementation of the java bean class ict.bean.Product... (c) Refer to the sample output... write code to complete the implementation of the servlet.", "pages": [4], "end_pos": 2800, "summary": "Description of a product information system using JSP, Servlet, and JavaBean components with implementation tasks.", "start_pos": 2219, "chunk_type": "overview", "has_examples": true, "main_concepts": ["CONC_006", "CONC_007", "CONC_011", "CONC_012", "CONC_013"], "has_definitions": true, "secondary_concepts": ["CONC_014"]}, {"id": "CHUNK_005", "text": "Q3 (a) State the methods in a servlet and briefly explain how the methods affect the servlet life cycle. [4%] (b) Briefly describe Four type of scope with respect to the accessibility in JEE application. [6%]", "pages": [5], "end_pos": 2945, "summary": "Questions about servlet lifecycle methods and JEE scoping mechanisms.", "start_pos": 2801, "chunk_type": "theoretical_question", "has_examples": false, "main_concepts": ["CONC_006", "CONC_016"], "has_definitions": true, "secondary_concepts": []}], "concepts": [{"id": "CONC_001", "title": "Java Server Page (JSP)", "aliases": ["JSP"], "keywords": ["JSP", "server-side", "dynamic content", "web development"], "confidence": 1.0, "difficulty": 4, "description": "Java Server Pages (JSP) is a server-side technology enabling developers to create dynamic web content by embedding Java code within HTML pages. It supports declarations, scriptlets, and expressions to generate dynamic responses. JSPs are compiled into servlets at runtime and used for view rendering in web applications.", "concept_type": "technology", "extracted_from": ["CHUNK_001"], "related_concepts": ["CONC_002", "CONC_003", "CONC_007"]}, {"id": "CONC_002", "title": "JSP Declaration", "aliases": ["JSP Declaration"], "keywords": ["declaration", "method", "variable", "JSP"], "confidence": 1.0, "difficulty": 3, "description": "JSP Declaration allows defining variables and methods within a JSP page using <%! %> syntax. These elements are part of the generated servlet class and persist across multiple requests, making them suitable for reusable utility methods like getAllMedals().", "concept_type": "component", "extracted_from": ["CHUNK_001"], "related_concepts": ["CONC_001", "CONC_008"]}, {"id": "CONC_003", "title": "JSP Scriptlet", "aliases": ["Scriptlet"], "keywords": ["scriptlet", "Java code", "logic", "execution"], "confidence": 1.0, "difficulty": 3, "description": "A JSP Scriptlet, enclosed in <% %>, contains executable Java code that runs when the page is requested. It is used to control flow, process data, or interact with backend logic such as calling methods from included files or processing user input.", "concept_type": "component", "extracted_from": ["CHUNK_002"], "related_concepts": ["CONC_001", "CONC_009"]}, {"id": "CONC_004", "title": "JSP Expression", "aliases": ["Expression"], "keywords": ["expression", "output", "display", "evaluation"], "confidence": 1.0, "difficulty": 3, "description": "A JSP Expression, written as <%= %>, evaluates a Java expression and outputs the result directly into the response stream. It is commonly used to display variable values dynamically on the rendered HTML page.", "concept_type": "component", "extracted_from": ["CHUNK_003"], "related_concepts": ["CONC_001"]}, {"id": "CONC_005", "title": "JSP Directive", "aliases": ["Directive"], "keywords": ["directive", "include", "page", "configuration"], "confidence": 1.0, "difficulty": 3, "description": "JSP Directives, specified with <%@ %>, provide instructions to the JSP container for page processing. Examples include include directives to embed other JSPs and page directives to configure error handling or content type.", "concept_type": "component", "extracted_from": ["CHUNK_002", "CHUNK_003"], "related_concepts": ["CONC_001", "CONC_010"]}, {"id": "CONC_006", "title": "Servlet", "aliases": ["Java Servlet"], "keywords": ["servlet", "request", "response", "lifecycle"], "confidence": 1.0, "difficulty": 4, "description": "A Java Servlet is a server-side component that handles client requests and generates dynamic responses. It follows a lifecycle managed by the container and is often used for business logic and request dispatching in Java EE web applications.", "concept_type": "component", "extracted_from": ["CHUNK_004"], "related_concepts": ["CONC_011", "CONC_012"]}, {"id": "CONC_007", "title": "JavaBean", "aliases": ["JavaBean"], "keywords": ["bean", "POJO", "serializable", "getter", "setter"], "confidence": 1.0, "difficulty": 3, "description": "A JavaBean is a reusable Java class that follows specific conventions: it is serializable, has a no-argument constructor, and provides getter/setter methods for properties. Used in JSP and servlets for data encapsulation and form handling.", "concept_type": "object", "extracted_from": ["CHUNK_004"], "related_concepts": ["CONC_006", "CONC_013"]}, {"id": "CONC_008", "title": "medalDB.jsp", "aliases": ["medalDB"], "keywords": ["medalDB.jsp", "utility", "method", "inclusion"], "confidence": 1.0, "difficulty": 3, "description": "A JSP file that defines utility methods via JSP declarations. Specifically, it implements the getAllMedals() method returning image paths for medals. It is included in other JSPs using directives to share functionality.", "concept_type": "component", "extracted_from": ["CHUNK_001"], "related_concepts": ["CONC_002", "CONC_005"]}, {"id": "CONC_009", "title": "q1.jsp", "aliases": ["q1.jsp"], "keywords": ["q1.jsp", "form", "table", "display"], "confidence": 1.0, "difficulty": 3, "description": "The main entry point JSP page displaying medal images in a table and an input form. It includes medalDB.jsp and uses scriptlets to render dynamic content based on shared methods.", "concept_type": "component", "extracted_from": ["CHUNK_002"], "related_concepts": ["CONC_003", "CONC_005", "CONC_008"]}, {"id": "CONC_010", "title": "q1Handler.jsp", "aliases": ["q1Handler"], "keywords": ["q1Handler.jsp", "validation", "processing", "output"], "confidence": 1.0, "difficulty": 4, "description": "A JSP responsible for processing user-submitted marks, validating input, determining the appropriate medal based on score ranges, and displaying results. It uses expressions to show output and redirects back via hyperlink.", "concept_type": "component", "extracted_from": ["CHUNK_003"], "related_concepts": ["CONC_004", "CONC_005", "CONC_006"]}, {"id": "CONC_011", "title": "ProductController Servlet", "aliases": ["ProductController"], "keywords": ["ProductController", "servlet", "handling", "database query"], "confidence": 1.0, "difficulty": 4, "description": "A servlet class named ict.servlet.ProductController that processes product inquiry forms. It retrieves selected product codes, queries the database via ProductDB, and outputs product details in HTML format.", "concept_type": "component", "extracted_from": ["CHUNK_004"], "related_concepts": ["CONC_006", "CONC_012"]}, {"id": "CONC_012", "title": "ProductDB Class", "aliases": ["ProductDB"], "keywords": ["ProductDB", "database", "query", "persistence"], "confidence": 1.0, "difficulty": 4, "description": "A Java class (ict.db.ProductDB) that encapsulates database operations for products. It provides methods like getProductByCode(String code) to retrieve product data and addProduct(Product p) to persist new entries.", "concept_type": "component", "extracted_from": ["CHUNK_004"], "related_concepts": ["CONC_011", "CONC_013"]}, {"id": "CONC_013", "title": "Product JavaBean", "aliases": ["Product"], "keywords": ["Product", "bean", "attributes", "form binding"], "confidence": 1.0, "difficulty": 3, "description": "A JavaBean class (ict.bean.Product) representing a product entity with attributes like code, description, and price. Implements Serializable and supports form binding in JSP/servlet workflows.", "concept_type": "object", "extracted_from": ["CHUNK_004"], "related_concepts": ["CONC_007", "CONC_012"]}, {"id": "CONC_014", "title": "Web Application Architecture", "aliases": ["Application Architecture"], "keywords": ["MVC", "layered", "presentation", "control", "model"], "confidence": 1.0, "difficulty": 5, "description": "Refers to the layered structure of the application involving JSP for presentation, JavaBeans for data modeling, and Servlets for control logic. Follows MVC-like patterns where components interact through defined interfaces and scopes.", "concept_type": "architecture", "extracted_from": ["CHUNK_001", "CHUNK_004"], "related_concepts": ["CONC_001", "CONC_006", "CONC_007"]}, {"id": "CONC_015", "title": "Input Validation", "aliases": ["Validation"], "keywords": ["validation", "input check", "error handling"], "confidence": 1.0, "difficulty": 3, "description": "Process of verifying user input before processing. In q1Handler.jsp, it checks if ''mark'' parameter exists and falls within valid numeric range. Ensures robustness and prevents errors in downstream logic.", "concept_type": "process", "extracted_from": ["CHUNK_003"], "related_concepts": ["CONC_010"]}, {"id": "CONC_016", "title": "Scope in JEE", "aliases": ["Scoping"], "keywords": ["scope", "visibility", "lifecycle", "JEE"], "confidence": 1.0, "difficulty": 4, "description": "Defines the visibility and lifecycle of objects in Java EE applications. Four types: page, request, session, and application scope. Determines how data is shared across components and users.", "concept_type": "theory", "extracted_from": ["CHUNK_005"], "related_concepts": []}], "relationships": [{"id": "REL_001", "type": "uses", "source": "CONC_009", "target": "CONC_008", "evidence"