Definition: A synchronous client to perform HTTP requests, exposing a simple, template method API over underlying HTTP client libraries.
Purpose: To consume RESTful web services.
Key Features:
Simple methods for HTTP requests (GET, POST, etc.)
Error handling
Customizable and extensible

