RestTemplate provides convenient methods to consume REST APIs and automatically convert the JSON (or other formats) responses into Java objects, commonly referred to as entities. This process is facilitated by HTTP message converters that Spring Boot configures automatically.

JSON   Java Object

[Full Slide OCR]:
Convert API Responses to Java Entities * RestTemplate provides convenient methods to consume REST APIs and automatically convert the JSON (or other formats) responses into Java objects, commonly referred to as entities. This process is facilitated by HTTP message converters that Spring Boot configures automatically. ° JSON € > Java Object

Suppose you have a REST API that returns details of a user and a corresponding Java entity class User. You can use RestTemplate to call the API and convert the JSON response directly into a User object.
public class User {
    private Long id;
    private String name;
    private String email;

    // Standard getters and setters
    public Long getId() {
        return id;
    }

    public void setId(Long id) {        this.id = id;    }

    public String getName() {
        return name;
    }
public void setName(String name) {        this.name = name;    }

    public String getEmail() {        return email;    }

    public void setEmail(String email) {        this.email = email;    }

    // toString method for debugging
    @Override
    public String toString() {
        return "User{" +
               "id=" + id +
               ", name=''" + name + ''\'''' +
               ", email=''" + email + ''\'''' +
               ''}'';
    }
}

