restTemplate.getForObject(url, User.class) makes an HTTP GET request to the specified URL.
It expects the response to be in JSON format that matches the User class structure.
RestTemplate uses the MappingJackson2HttpMessageConverter (or similar) to automatically deserialize the JSON response into a User object.

