RestTemplate provides a simple yet powerful way to implement synchronous calls between microservices in a Spring Boot application. It can be extended to support patterns essential for robust microservice architectures, including service discovery, resilience, and secure communication.
It''s also worth considering WebClient, which supports asynchronous operations and is positioned as a modern alternative to RestTemplate for microservices communication.

