[Full Page OCR]:
Roles of Memento Pattern * The Memento Pattern attempts to solve this problem by having privileged access to the state of the object you want to save. * Memento preserves encapsulation by letting the Originator create and restore its own state. Caretaker never modifies the state directly.

ITP4507 - Contemporary Topics in Software Engineering
6
• Other objects have only a more restricted access to the object, thus 
preserving their encapsulation. This pattern defines three roles of 
objects:
• The Originator is the object whose state we want to save.
• The Memento is another object that saves the state of the Originator.
• The Caretaker manages the timing of the saving of the state, saves the Memento 
and, if needed, uses Memento to restore the state of the Originator.
