24
After three saves:
undoList (top → bottom): [ "Hello World!!!", "Hello World", "Hello" ]
redoList: []
Undo:
- Move top of undoList → redoList
- Restore new top of undoList
Result: "Hello World"
Redo:
- Pop from redoList, restore it
- Push it back onto undoList
Result: "Hello World!!!"
How the Stacks Work
The top of undoList is the current state. Undo moves the current snapshot to redoList 
and restores the new top (previous state). Redo pops from redoList, restores it, then 
pushes it back to undoList.

