ITP4507 - Contemporary Topics in Software Engineering
26
• Undo does nothing: you restored the current snapshot;
 
 
 
 
instead, pop → redo, then restore new top.
• Redo broken after new edit: you forgot to clear redoList in save().
• Too many saves: save only after meaningful edits (keystroke batching, 
blur events).
• Leaky encapsulation: 
keep state access limited to Originator ↔ Memento collaboration 
(package scope here, or inner classes in stricter designs).
Common Pitfalls

