ing, Changing, and Tables interfaces, and can raise exceptions to handle errors globally.\",\"concept_type\":\"component\",\"extracted_from\":[\"CHUNK_006\"],\"related_concepts\":[\"CONC_004\"]},{\"id\":\"CONC_009\",\"title\":\"Macro Definition\",\"aliases\":[\"ABAP Macro\"],\"keywords\":[\"Macro\",\"DEFINE\",\"Code Reuse\"],\"confidence\":0.9,\"difficulty\":3,\"description\":\"Code snippets defined in ABAP using DEFINE...ENDOFDEFINITION to reduce repetition and simplify report logic. Macros are processed before compilation.\",\"concept_type\":\"process\",\"extracted_from\":[\"CHUNK_006\"],\"related_concepts\":[\"CONC_004\"]}]"', '"[{\"id\":\"REL_001\",\"type\":\"supports\",\"source\":\"CONC_002\",\"target\":\"CONC_006\",\"evidence\":\"Question 1(d) asks about the level of Decision Making that a DSS supports.\",\"strength\":1,\"bidirectional\":false},{\"id\":\"REL_002\",\"type\":\"implements\",\"source\":\"CONC_003\",\"target\":\"CONC_001\",\"evidence\":\"CRM is described as strategic software used to manage relationships, often part of broader Enterprise Software suites.\",\"strength\":0.8,\"bidirectional\":false},{\"id\":\"REL_003\",\"type\":\"uses\",\"source\":\"CONC_004\",\"target\":\"CONC_008\",\"evidence\":\"Function modules are called within ABAP programs (Question 5).\",\"strength\":1,\"bidirectional\":false},{\"id\":\"REL_004\",\"type\":\"interacts_with\",\"source\":\"CONC_004\",\"target\":\"CONC_007\",\"evidence\":\"ABAP code defines and queries table structures (Questions 3 & 4).\",\"strength\":1,\"bidirectional\":true},{\"id\":\"REL_005\",\"type\":\"references\",\"source\":\"CONC_007\",\"target\":\"CONC_009\",\"evidence\":\"Both utilize logical definitions within ABAP programs to structure data flow.\",\"strength\":0.5,\"bidirectional\":false},{\"id\":\"REL_006\",\"type\":\"part_of\",\"source\":\"CONC_005\",\"target\":\"CONC_001\",\"evidence\":\"Work processes exist in the Application Layer of the ERP system architecture.\",\"strength\":1,\"bidirectional