Question 1 
 
 
You are the owner of an interior design company, Grand Level (GL), which specializes in 
creating unique and functional spaces for businesses, one of your clients, is a chain of boutique 
hotels. All Seasons Group (ASG) and it is looking to revamp their interiors to provide a more 
upscale and luxurious experience for their guests. 
 
(a) Your team has been tasked with designing the interiors of the ASG’s flagship property 
in a major city. As you work on the project, you realize that there are several decisions 
that need to be made at different levels of decision making - strategic, tactical, and 
operational - to ensure the project is a success.  
 
For each of the following questions that ask for different information for decisions, state 
the level of decision making they are trying to make: 
 
(i) Should ASG focus on creating a consistent design across all their hotels, or should 
each hotel have a unique design to reflect its location and culture? 
(ii) How can the design of the hotel rooms be optimized to increase guest comfort and 
satisfaction? 
(iii) What materials and finishes should be used in the hotel lobby to create a welcoming 
and luxurious atmosphere? 
(iv) How can the lighting design be improved to enhance the overall ambiance of the 
hotel? 
(v) Should ASG invest in technology upgrades such as smart room controls and 
automated check-in systems to improve the guest experience?              [5 marks] 
 
(b) What are the names of the FOUR functions of business management used by managers 
and key leaders to meet the challenges of the demanding business world? 
[4 marks] 
 
(c) Customer Relationship Management (CRM) is a new strategic software used by the 
interior design company, GL, to manage the relationship and interaction with its 
customers. 
 
Suggest and briefly describe TWO features of CRM that help GL to improve the 
relationship with its customers and increase revenue. 
[6 marks] 
 
(d) GL is also planning to use Decision Support System (DSS) to enhance it management 
decision process. 
 
(i) What is the level of Decision Making that a DSS supports? Give one reason.  
 
[2 marks] 
(ii) Suggest THREE features of DSSs that help decision making in GL.  
[3 marks] 
 
 
 
 
