What are microservices?
•
Microservices architecture involves smaller applications deployed 
independently as loosely coupled services, tied together through 
application integration
•
Microservices is a service-oriented architecture pattern wherein 
applications are built as a collection of various smallest 
independent service units. 
•
software engineering approach 
•
focuses on decomposing an application into single-function 
modules with well-defined interfaces. 
•
Each modules can be independently deployed and operated by 
small teams that own the entire lifecycle of the service.

E-commerce application
•
An e-commerce application that
•
takes orders from customers, 
•
verifies inventory and available credit, 
•
and ships them. 
•
The application consists of several components including the 
StoreFrontUI, 
•
implements the user interface, 
•
along with some backend services 
•
checking credit, 
•
maintaining inventory 
•
shipping orders. 
•
The application consists of a set of services.
•

The application consists of a set of services.

Features of microservices
•
Microservices structures an application as a collection of 
services that are
•
Highly maintainable and testable
•
Loosely coupled
•
Independently deployable
•
Organized around business capabilities
•
Owned by a small team
