Benefits of Microservice Architecture
•
microservices can be simpler to develop. 
•
small scope makes it easier for developers to improve them 
through continuous integration and continuous delivery (CI/CD). 
•
microservices can be written in any programming language and 
can communicate with other microservices through APIs.
•
APIs make it simpler to develop integrated applications
•
It enables the rapid, frequent and reliable delivery of large, 
complex applications. 
•
It also enables an organization to evolve its technology stack.

Strengths of the Microservice 
Architecture
•
Independent components.
•
Services are deployed and updated independently. It more flexibility. 
•
bug in one microservice only an impact on a particular service and does not influence the entire 
application. 
•
it is much easier to add new features
