How it work?

WebClient
•
WebClient is a non-blocking, reactive HTTP client introduced in 
Spring WebFlux (Spring Framework 5)
•
Provides a modern, functional programming API for performing 
HTTP requests
•
Replaces the RestTemplate API from Spring MVC for reactive and 
non-blocking applications
•
Supports reactive programming with the use of Flux and Mono 
types from Project Reactor
•
Offers advanced features like filtering, custom error handling, and 
request/response transformation

Create a WebClient
•
Use the WebClient.builder() or WebClient.create() methods
•
Can be configured with base URLs, headers, and other settings
WebClient webClient = WebClient.builder() .baseUrl("http://api.example.com") 
.defaultHeader(HttpHeaders.CONTENT_TYPE, 
MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON_VALUE) .build();

Performing HTTP Request
•
Supports various HTTP methods: GET, POST, PUT, DELETE, etc.
•
Allows URI templating and URI variable substitution
•
Can handle request/response body conversion and content 
negotiation
Mono<String> response = webClient.get() 
.uri("/resource/{id}", "123") 
.retrieve() 
.bodyToMono(String.class); 
response.subscribe(System.out::println);

Reactive and Non-block 
Capabilities
•
WebClient returns Mono or Flux instances for asynchronous and 
non-blocking processing
•
Can be integrated with other reactive components in the 
application
•
Offers backpressure support and resource management

Error Handling
•
Handle errors using 
onErrorReturn(), 
onErrorResume(), or 
doOnError()
•
Filter and transform requests 
and responses using 
ExchangeFilterFunction
•
Integrate with other Spring 
Cloud components for service 
discovery, load balancing, and 
more
WebClient.get() 
.uri("/resource/{id}", "123")
.retrieve() 
.onStatus(HttpStatus::is4xxClientError, response -> Mono.error(new 
CustomException("Client error"))) 
.onStatus(HttpStatus::is5xxServerError, response -> Mono.error(new 
CustomException("Server error"))) 
.bodyToMono(String.class) 
.subscribe(System.out::println, Throwable::printStackTrace)

